        <h2>Networking at a bts concert!</h2>
        <h5>Selfies were taken at United center and Solider Field in Chicago </h5>
    </CENTER>
    <center><img src="~/images/selfie1 .jpeg" alt="Alternate Text" width="680" height="480"></center>

    <p>
        They are not just a group of idols who just perform on stage and that is all they do but there are other things they have proven that they are defiantly no ordinary
        group. Lets start off with the fact that they began their career passing around flyers for fans to watch them perform and they have collected a small group of followers. From
        there on they rose to the very top and became Top social artists who have dominated worldwide. Starting from the beginning of 2013 where they have debuted in their music
        video song "No more dream" BTS have paved their way to the top. At first they began in a small company known as 1totheK which is a Korean variety channel that promotes their song up until
        the BTS wings era which they were promoted to ibighit a different Korean pop music company channel.
    </p>

    <center><img src="~/images/btsworld1.jpg" alt="Alternate Text" width="680" height="480"></center>

    <p>
        Thanks to this kind of community I met many amazing friends I am able to connect with who share the same common interest and of course the same taste in music. This is one of those
        networking events where it doesn't even take much effort because all you have to do is ask somone who their bias is and next thing you know you end up in a group chat
        talking about this with five other people. This is the kind of culture bts has created and because they are so influential and inspirational they have the power to use it for good or evil. However
        they decide to bring their fans closer together through events like this.
    </p>

    <center><img src="~/images/selca1.jpg" alt="Alternate Text" width="680" height="480"></center>

    <p>
        So what is it like networking at a bts concert? All I can say if you know bts you can make friends pretty fast before the show starts. Majority of the people there are very friendly and some even hand out
        free merchandise! Even when you are waiting in line you can make a friend on the spot. For some they are willing to just hand you freebies and others like to exchnage goodies so there are a few different type of
        people out there but most of them are friendly. I just have to say a venue like this doesn't happen often! It still amazes me that you can be in a room full of people who literally have the same amount of interest
        as you.
    </p>
</div>

