<div class="card">
    <CENTER>
        <b><h1>The merch culture</h1></b>
    </CENTER>

    <p>
        As the saying goes "When you have money there is nothing to buy and when you don't have any money there is always something you want." That is
        so true because it always happens. Are you the type of shopper that likes to buy one item from a set series or buys the whole set? What if they release a item
        from BTS that makes you want to collect everything? Here are the top 5 BTS merch that collectors normally buy.
    </p>

    <b><center><h1>1. Albums</h1></center></b>

    <center><img src="~/images/albums.jpg" alt="blog 2" /></center>
    <center>
        <p>
            Yes people love to collect albums and while there are those fans who rather just listen to the music for free for those who wants hands on merch to collect they
            look forward to the albums. Inside the album there's a large poster, various photocards and sometimes other extra goodies such as stickers and special notes. This is why albums are soughtly seeked
            after especially the older editions.
        </p>
    </center>

    <center><h2>2. Coffee coffee coffee</h2></center>
    <center><img src="~/images/btscoffee.jpg" alt="Alternate Text" style="height:250px;"></center>

    <center>
        <p>
            Instead of grabbing a average cup of joe for the morning why not have some bts coffee for a change? Yes it is just
            coffee but the way they market it is what makes it very appealing. Meet BTS COFFEE! This is their line of coffee and it is a very
            popular selling item in Korea. Collect all seven members as each flavor is different and they all have a unique
            design on it.
        </p>
    </center>

    <center><h2>3. BTS cola cola cola~</h2></center>
    <center><img src="~/images/cola.jpg" alt="Alternate Text" width="600" height="600"></center>

    <center>
        <p>
            Coca cola is also another beverage bts has been working with in their photoshoots to promote this product. Although coca cola is already a popular
            brand. Yes there is a all out photoshoot just for coca cola but it is really amazing to see how well they market this product.
        </p>
    </center>

    <b><center><h2>4. Posters</h2></center></b>
    <center><img src="~/images/posterset.jpg" alt="Alternate Text" style="height:250px;"></center>

    <center>
        <p>
            Yes posters are colletibles because there are some exclusive versions that can only be obtained through concerts, albums, stores, or even just online purchases. When it comes
            to posters they are the most sought after simply because people like to use it for decoration. Sometimes when I see how other people decorate their room
            it really inspires me to decorate as well. Although posters might be the easiest merch item to obtain if you want a certian poster the price for it can really rack up and depending
            on the member the value price for it will be able to change.
        </p>
    </center>

    <center><h2>5. Lightsticks</h2></center>
    <center><img src="~/images/merch.jpg" alt="Alternate Text" style="height:250px;"></center>
    <center>
        <p>
            Lightsticks are a essential especially if you are attending a concert or if you just like to collect them all. They usually update their lightstick
            style yearly and so fans always like to get the new one simply because of new functions. Although you can still enter into the concert whether your lightstick is the newest
            one or not there is no difference other than the style upgrade. Lightsticks also come with more items in it such as photocards, stickers, and sometimes other
            random goodies that makes it even more appealing. For BTS the name of their lightstick is ARMY BOMB which is a glowing bomb that changes colors. During concerts there are projects fans
            do such as: Rainbow ocean wave, purple wave, letter wave where they create words using their lightsticks.
        </p>
    </center>

